title: No. 2 Bulldogs Fall in Season Opener
text:
No. 2 Bulldogs Fall in Season Opener 
By Norman Seawright III October 10, 2015 Updated Oct 10, 2015 at 10:44 PM CDT 
Bemidji, MN (NNCNOW.com) -- The University of Minnesota-Duluth (UMD) men's hockey team opened its season with a loss at Bemidji State University (BSU) for Scott Sandelin's 600th game as Bulldog Head Coach. 
Kasimir Kaskisuo held 30 saves and led first behind a shorthanded Andy Welinski goal, but the Beavers outpaced the Bulldogs to win 3-2 (including a late goal in the final period).
